<br>
However, monk empirical evidence suggests that 1400 is where diminishing returns start to occur.<br>
<br>
What I have personally noted, and again I wish I was a log fiend, but I've used it as a rule of thumb is that one should go for the century marks.<br>
<br>
no diff between 1120 and 1180 ac, but a diff between 1160 and 1201.  Maybe those were bad examples, but go for centuries.<br>
<br>
Of course, if you can get 1400 ac, you generally have some pretty decent equipment with hp on it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/usoheiyoshi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sohei Yoshi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/12/02 3:24:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylummonk.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Iksar monk worth it?</span><hr size=1> Having a little knowledge of some armor classes and what affect it has on reducing damage I offer this. A while ago on a server far far away I had the most fun time of being test subject in a little self experiment. Take this as what you will.<br>
<br>
Warrior lvl 60 AC 1205, 3589HP all no buffs. Vs Test mob (Sir Lucan) Same level every spawn.<br>
Average hit from Target: 89<br>
Number of Times hit Warrior before reaching 0-hp: 37<br>
<br>
Warrior lvl 60 AC 1352, 4302HP all no buffs, Vs Test mob (Sir Lucan) Same level every spawn.<br>
Average hit from Target: 78<br>
Number of Times hit Warrior before reaching 713-hp:45<br>
<br>
<br>
Timing this experiment out at 713 hp was to reduce the experiment to AC so it would not affect number of hits.<br>
<br>
Conclusion after this was 147 raw AC increase showed that average hits were reduced by 11 points.<br>
It offers the warrior 8 additional hits before 0 hp is reached.<br>
<br>
This really does nothing to help anyone out with gear or getting better gear. I think it shows only this. HP &gt; AC at 60. But we all knew that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
